losaka, who was also called the Germinator, was a great spirit of the folklore and myth of the Azuposi people of the Pasocada Basin of northern Maztica.
The Germinator was called into being by the song of Sussistinako, the Spider Woman. As a spirit of creation, Alosaka helped make all of the flowers, animals, and other life forms found within the Pasocada Basin.
